cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.SI, cs.SD 

The paper deals with disambiguating author names in large bibliographic data sets, which involves analyzing citation and author graphs. This suggests that the paper could fall under several sub-categories, including cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.DB (Databases), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.SD (Software Engineering). However, given the focus on citation networks and similarity metrics, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
